Meet <b>Daniel</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Daniel lives at <a href='/home/?user=galendaeus'>5137 Pyramid Drive</a>, in the historical neighborhood of Ravenwood. Daniel's only been a citizen since December 4th of last year, but he's already made himself right at home!<br><br>The Ravenwood area holds a special measure of interest for Daniel, since he's quite interested in the field of archeology. During his time here, Daniel has come to truly appreciate all of the historical landmarks and beautiful architecture that can be found throughout Millsberry, especially in his very own neighborhood! Daniel has become fast friends with Edna Nelson of the Millsberry Historical Society, with whom he's often discussed how Millsberry used to look before the Great Fire destroyed many of the town's older buildings.<br><br>Daniel also studies foreign languages at the Millsberry Academy, and hopes to one day have a chance to go abroad on a real archeology dig. Additionally, Daniel is a very hard worker, which has helped him become an excellent student.<br><br>Science fiction is another of Daniel's many interests. At dusk, he just loves staring up at the stars in the dark blue sky (his favorite color) and imagining all sorts of cool things, like great space battles.<br><br>On weekends, Daniel likes hanging out at his best friend's house, where they often enjoy listening to classic rock. When being indoors gets too stuffy, he and his friends often enjoy walking around the zoo. During the summer, they'll often stop by Scoop's ice cream parlor. Supposedly, Daniel and his friends are very excited about the rumor that Chocolate Lucky Charms may soon be available as an ice cream topping!<br><br>Congratulations on being a remarkable citizen, Daniel!</div>
